# Pre-Commit / Pre-Push Checklist

Before running `git commit` or `git push`, verify the following files are in sync with the current tool count and new tools added.

## When a new tool is added to `lib/tools.ts`

1. **`README.md`** — bump the tool count ("All N tools run 100% client-side") and add the new tool under the correct category section.

2. **`public/llms.txt`** — add the new tool under the correct category section with its slug path. This file is manually maintained and does NOT auto-sync.

3. **`app/sitemap.ts`** — bump `LAST_MODIFIED` to today's date (`YYYY-MM-DD`). This is the only part of the sitemap that requires manual updates; the URL list auto-syncs from `tools`.

4. **`app/tools/[slug]/ToolPageClient.tsx`** — register the new tool slug in `TOOL_MAP` with a `next/dynamic` import.

## Files that auto-sync (no manual update needed)

- `app/sitemap.ts` URL list — auto-maps over `tools`
- `app/page.tsx` FAQ answer — uses `tools.length`
- `app/about/page.tsx` OG description — uses `tools.length`
- `components/HomepageClient.tsx` hero copy — uses `tools.length`
- Homepage category filter and ⌘K command palette — auto-derive from `CATEGORY_ORDER` / `tools`

## Quick sanity check before committing

```bash
# Confirm README count matches actual tool count
grep "All [0-9]* tools" README.md
grep -c "  {$" lib/tools.ts   # should match the number above
```
